cus%20on%20campaigning%2C%20his%20second%20in%20charge%2C%20Flanagan%2C%20would%20take%20charge%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.revisor.mn.gov%2Fconstitution%2F%23article_5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMinnesota's%20constitution.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20doing%20so%2C%20Flanagan%20would%20make%20history%20as%20the%20first%20woman%20governor%20of%20Minnesota%20and%20the%20first%20Native%20American%20woman%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20assume%20the%20role%20of%20governor%20in%20any%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Flanagan's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmn.gov%2Fgovernor%2Fabout-gov%2Fpeggyflanagan%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eofficial%20biography%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20White%20Earth%20Band%20of%20Ojibwe%20and%20the%20highest-ranking%20Native%20woman%20elected%20to%20an%20executive%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlanagan%20began%20her%20political%20career%20in%202002%20working%20for%20former%20US%20Sen.%20Paul%20Wellstone's%20campaign%2C%20per%20the%20MinnPost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20between%202005%20and%202009%2C%20she%20became%20the%20first%20Native%20American%20on%20the%20board%20of%20the%20Minneapolis%20Board%20of%20Education%2C%20MinnPost%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20a%20handful%20of%20jobs%2C%20including%20working%20at%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20trained%20future%20organizers%20and%20politicians%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Walz%20himself%20%E2%80%94%20Flanagan%20ran%20unopposed%20for%20the%20Minnesota%20House%20representatives%20in%202015%20and%20won.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%202017%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-leaders-respond-kamala-harris-selects-tim-walz-vp-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWalz%3C%2Fa%3E%20picked%20her%20to%20run%20alongside%20him%20for%20his%202018%20Gubernatorial%20campaign.%20The%20pair%20defeated%20Donald%20Trump-endorsed%20candidate%20Jeff%20Johnson%20with%2054%25%20of%20the%20vote.%