This%20also%20increases%20micro-organisms%20in%20the%20soil%2C%20works%20as%20a%20biofertiliser%2C%20and%20provides%20a%20congenial%20environment%20for%20the%20release%20of%20nutrients%20by%20decomposing%20the%20plant%2Fcrop%20residue%20in%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20they%20have%20also%20planted%20%E2%80%98nitrogen%20fixer%E2%80%99%20plants%20like%20mustard%20and%20clover%2C%20which%20are%20also%20used%20for%20mulching.%20The%20Bansal%20family%20also%20does%20mulching%20thrice%20a%20year%20with%20the%20grass%20grown%20in%20their%20orchard.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMulching%20is%20an%20agricultural%20practice%20where%20an%20area%20of%20soil%20is%20covered%20with%20grass%20and%20other%20farm%20waste%20which%20decomposes%20and%20improves%20the%20soil%20health.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20did%20a%20course%20in%20permaculture%20from%20Aranya%20Agricultural%20Alternatives%20in%20Hyderabad.%20Permaculture%20(permanent%20agriculture)%20is%20the%20harmonious%20integration%20of%20nature%20and%20humans%3B%20where%20one%20lives%20with%20nature%2C%20instead%20of%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPermaculture%20is%20a%20way%20of%20living.%20Today%2C%20most%20people%20follow%20monocropping.%20Take%20a%20look%20at%20any%20forest%2C%20you%E2%80%99ll%20find%20different%20kinds%20of%20plants%20growing%20together.%20No%20jungle%20will%20have%20just%20one%20plant%20or%20animal.%20Soil%20health%20and%20quality%20is%20spoilt%20because%20of%20monoculture.%20If%20you%20grow%20different%20crops%20together%2C%20even%20if%20one%20is%20spoiled%2C%20the%20other%20will%20survive%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Aprajita.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20explains%20that%20the%20soil%20health%20improves%20as%20well.%20She%20is%20now%20working%20on%20creating%20a%20food%20forest%20on%20a%20small%20portion%20of%20her%20parents%E2%80%99%20land.%20Here%2C%20she%20is%20growing%20different%20varieties%20of%20native%20trees%20and%20plants.%20She%20collects%20heirloom%20see